<caption id="DF3D15D9361DD07556E4F868FE864CBE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488036" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6488036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488036/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" startId="23.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[178,1409,181,1918]" targetPageId="23">
<paragraph id="8BFD4551361DD07556E4F868FE864CBE" blockId="23.[151,1436,1943,2039]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="B9369943361DD07556E4F868FE754CE6" bold="true" box="[151,334,1943,1967]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">FIGURES 83–89</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED2361DD075572FF868FD8D4CE6" authority="Singh" authorityName="Singh" authorityYear="2022" box="[348,694,1943,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Quadrastichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manmohani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9369943361DD075572FF868FD4A4CE6" box="[348,625,1943,1967]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Quadrastichus manmohani</emphasis>
Singh
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B9369943361DD07554B2F868FC294CE6" bold="true" box="[705,786,1943,1967]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2052438361DD07554B2F868FC294CE6" box="[705,786,1943,1967]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 83–84, female: 83, ovipositor; 84, distal part of ovipositor enlarged to show cercal setae. 85–89, male: 85, body in dorso-lateral view; 86, body in lateral view; 87, antenna; 88, mesosoma in dorsal view; 89, forewing.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513612D07A56B4FF68FCD84A2C" blockId="24.[151,1437,150,1834]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Mesosoma (
<figureCitation id="137959D43612D07A573CFF68FE9B4BF8" box="[335,416,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 74–82" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-22@22.[151,1436,181,1740]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 74–82. Quadrastichus manmohani Singh sp. nov., female: 74, body in dorsal view; 75, body in lateral view; 76, antenna; 77, part of antenna showing anelli; 78, distal segments of club showing apical spine; 79, mesosoma in dorsal view; 80, forewing; 81, part of forewing showing dorsal seta on SMV; 82, part of forewing venation showing postmarginal and stigmal veins." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488034" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488034/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
) 1.3× as long as wide (595: 457). Pronotum 0.4× as long as mesoscutum (103: 232). Mesoscutum 1.9× as wide as long (457: 232), 1.4× as long as scutellum (232: 162). Scutellum 1.6× as wide as long (258: 162), 4× dorsellum length (40); submedian lines approximately twice as far from each other as from sublateral line, enclosing a space about 1.4× as long as wide. Propodeum medially 1.3× as long as dorsellum (41: 30). Forewing (
<figureCitation id="137959D43612D07A56D3FED8FE264A08" box="[160,285,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 74–82" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-22@22.[151,1436,181,1740]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 74–82. Quadrastichus manmohani Singh sp. nov., female: 74, body in dorsal view; 75, body in lateral view; 76, antenna; 77, part of antenna showing anelli; 78, distal segments of club showing apical spine; 79, mesosoma in dorsal view; 80, forewing; 81, part of forewing showing dorsal seta on SMV; 82, part of forewing venation showing postmarginal and stigmal veins." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488034" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488034/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 80, 82</figureCitation>
) 2.2× as long as wide (1234: 553); marginal vein as long as costal cell (304), 3.5× as long as stigmal vein (304: 87); postmarginal vein about two-thirds of stigmal vein (56: 87).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513612D07A56B4FE90FA7B4A98" blockId="24.[151,1437,150,1834]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Gaster (
<figureCitation id="137959D43612D07A5753FE90FE984AC0" box="[288,419,366,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 74–82" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-22@22.[151,1436,181,1740]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 74–82. Quadrastichus manmohani Singh sp. nov., female: 74, body in dorsal view; 75, body in lateral view; 76, antenna; 77, part of antenna showing anelli; 78, distal segments of club showing apical spine; 79, mesosoma in dorsal view; 80, forewing; 81, part of forewing showing dorsal seta on SMV; 82, part of forewing venation showing postmarginal and stigmal veins." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488034" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488034/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 74, 75</figureCitation>
) narrower than mesosoma; 1.2× as long as mesosoma; Gt7 2× as long as exserted part of ovipositor, postcercale 0.5× of Gt7. Hypopygium reaching about middle of gaster. Ovipositor sheaths (
<figureCitation id="137959D43612D07A5379FE6CFA604AE4" box="[1290,1371,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–89" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-20@23.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 83–89. Quadrastichus manmohani Singh, sp. nov., 83–84, female: 83, ovipositor; 84, distal part of ovipositor en- larged to show cercal setae. 85–89, male: 85, body in dorso-lateral view; 86, body in lateral view; 87, antenna; 88, mesosoma in dorsal view; 89, forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488036/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
) 0.2× as long as ovipositor length (182: 812), exserted part of ovipositor sheaths as long as postcercale (
<figureCitation id="137959D43612D07A52ACFE48FA0F4A98" box="[1247,1332,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–89" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-20@23.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 83–89. Quadrastichus manmohani Singh, sp. nov., 83–84, female: 83, ovipositor; 84, distal part of ovipositor en- larged to show cercal setae. 85–89, male: 85, body in dorso-lateral view; 86, body in lateral view; 87, antenna; 88, mesosoma in dorsal view; 89, forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488036/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513612D07A56B4FE24FC214ABC" blockId="24.[151,1437,150,1834]" box="[199,794,474,501]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
MALE (
<figureCitation id="137959D43612D07A5756FE24FE934ABC" box="[293,424,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–89" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-20@23.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 83–89. Quadrastichus manmohani Singh, sp. nov., 83–84, female: 83, ovipositor; 84, distal part of ovipositor en- larged to show cercal setae. 85–89, male: 85, body in dorso-lateral view; 86, body in lateral view; 87, antenna; 88, mesosoma in dorsal view; 89, forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488036/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 85–89</figureCitation>
). Body size 
<quantity id="4CBAE8B43612D07A5441FE24FDAD4ABC" box="[562,662,475,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.16" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="1.16">1.16 mm</quantity>
(dry, n = 1)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513612D07A56B4FE00FDC64928" blockId="24.[151,1437,150,1834]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B93699433612D07A56B4FE00FEB94950" box="[199,386,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Color/Sculpture.</emphasis>
Similar to female except anterior half of propodeum, Gt2 laterally, a wide stripe across on Gt5 and Gt6 black to dark brown. Antenna scape pale yellow, remainder yellow with light brown tinge; whorls of long, light brown setae on flagellar and basal club segments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513612D07A56B4FD94FA2A48C8" blockId="24.[151,1437,150,1834]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B93699433612D07A56B4FD94FE0D49CC" box="[199,310,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Structure.</emphasis>
Head clearly wider than mesosoma (409: 372); in frontal view 1.3× as wide as high (380: 300), 1.8× as wide as frontovertex (380: 211); malar space about 0.6× as long as eye length (111: 172), mouth 1.3× as wide as malar space length (148: 111); toruli their own length above a line joining the lower margins of the eyes. In dorsal view POL 2× OOL (87: 42). Antenna (
<figureCitation id="137959D43612D07A543AFD28FDA149B8" box="[585,666,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–89" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-20@23.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 83–89. Quadrastichus manmohani Singh, sp. nov., 83–84, female: 83, ovipositor; 84, distal part of ovipositor en- larged to show cercal setae. 85–89, male: 85, body in dorso-lateral view; 86, body in lateral view; 87, antenna; 88, mesosoma in dorsal view; 89, forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488036/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 87</figureCitation>
) with one anellus; scape 4.2× as long as wide (188: 45), with plaque covering middle 0.5× of distal half of ventral margin; pedicel about 1.7× as long as wide (67: 36); funicle 4-segmented, vase shaped; F1 shortest, 1.4× (61: 42), F2 2.42× (85: 35), F3 2.3× (94: 40) and F4 2.5× (90: 36) as long as wide. Club 3-segmented, as long as basal 3 funicle segments combined; C1 2× (68: 33), C2 2.7× (79: 29) and C3 4.2× (109: 26) as long as wide. Terminal spine about as long as C3 width (23: 26), without apical seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513612D07A56B4FC74FB844F58" blockId="24.[151,1437,150,1834]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Mesosoma 1.4× as long as wide (531: 372); pronotum 2.4× as long as wide (255: 106); mesoscutum 2× as long as pronotum, 1.7× as wide as long (372: 213); scutellum 1.3× as wide as long (191: 149), about 3.5× dorsellum length (149: 43). Propodeum 1.3× as long as dorsellum (88: 43). Forewing (
<figureCitation id="137959D43612D07A5588FC2CFB7548A4" box="[1019,1102,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–89" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-20@23.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 83–89. Quadrastichus manmohani Singh, sp. nov., 83–84, female: 83, ovipositor; 84, distal part of ovipositor en- larged to show cercal setae. 85–89, male: 85, body in dorso-lateral view; 86, body in lateral view; 87, antenna; 88, mesosoma in dorsal view; 89, forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488036/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 89</figureCitation>
) 2.1× as long as wide (1008: 488); marginal vein 1.1× as long as costal cell (300: 261), 4× as long as stigmal vein (300: 74).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513612D07A56B4FBE4FA764F10" blockId="24.[151,1437,150,1834]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Gaster (
<figureCitation id="137959D43612D07A5752FBE4FE9F4F7F" box="[289,420,1050,1078]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–89" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-20@23.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 83–89. Quadrastichus manmohani Singh, sp. nov., 83–84, female: 83, ovipositor; 84, distal part of ovipositor en- larged to show cercal setae. 85–89, male: 85, body in dorso-lateral view; 86, body in lateral view; 87, antenna; 88, mesosoma in dorsal view; 89, forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488036/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 85, 86</figureCitation>
) 1.2× as long as mesosoma (659: 531); genitalia (
<figureCitation id="137959D43612D07A5597FBE4FB524F7F" box="[996,1129,1050,1078]" captionStart="FIGURES 61–66" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[172,1411,561,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-239@18.[172,1415,561,1949]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 61–66. Aprostocetus dehradunensis Singh sp. nov., male: 61, body in dorso-lateral view; 62, head in frontal view; 63, antenna; 64. forewing; 65, genitalia; 66, distal part of genitalia showing digitus spines." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488030/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 65, 66</figureCitation>
), aedeagus 0.8× as long as phallobase length (213: 270), phallobase 3.7× as long as wide (270: 73), digitus with one long digital spine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513612D07A56B4FB9DFB594FE8" blockId="24.[151,1437,150,1834]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B93699433612D07A56B4FB9DFE044F35" bold="true" box="[199,319,1122,1148]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Variation.</emphasis>
There is variation in sizes for both sexes. No color variations, except dark brown to black spot on anterio-lateral side of propodeum in some specimens, were observed in the specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
